Dubaiiiiiiii! 
Oh me, Oh my! 

Hard times have come
Upon your shore
The skies are dark
And overcast
 Perhaps will be forever more

You wonder now
How long ‘twill last
I see you mourning
Hear your cries
Your bitter wailing
Strangled sighs

You clench your fist 
and grit your teeth
And can’t believe
The hand of fate
that you must greet 

Dubaiiii! Dubaiii!
Oh me oh my!
Do tell us please
We wonder why 
and truly want to know
If what you reap 
Is what you sow

Empty towers
crowd your sky
 once so bright
sadly now
bereft of light

Dark hulls against 
the naked night
once testimony
of your might

You enslaved millions
Why oh why
You spat on them and made them cry
Your whips were wealth
and wrath and stealth
And tyranny without the belt

You stole their souls
And built your city
Without comfort
Without pity

 Pharaohs come 
And pharaohs go
You’re a pharaoh
You should know
Bricks without straw
Yes, you should know.
You never let my people go!
Oh Moses, Moses
Where are you?

They wept and worked
In stifling heat  
 Fell off buildings at your feet
Died in contempt
And defeat

 But times have changed
Alas we’re here
Faced with life
And what we must
Faced with fate and what we trust

The Ides  of March
has touched Dubai
So hark the whisper,
roar and the cry

Of Dubai’s pharaohs
In denial
Aghast, astounded and confused
Aghast, confounded and contused
What’s your history 
What’s your past 
Nothing built in sin will last


Goodbye Dubai!
Oh me, oh my!
Your hollow echoes rise and die

Will you ever rise again
That’s the thing we’d like to know
Maybe yes; and maybe no!
In the meantime
Dust to dust
Sand to sand
And rust to rust

And just in case
You didn’t know
Lambos dying in the dust
Glory does not always last

Goodbye Dubai!
Oh me , oh my!
Will you ever rise again
This will be the sad refrain.
Karma always seeks a price
The take-away is just be nice.

Millions, trillions cannot save you,
Just God’s Gracious Grace upon you.
 Never, never, be unjust.
God will enter when He must. 

Goodbye Dubai!
Oh me, oh my!
Dubai’s done, I wonder why
Will she ever rise again?
That will be the sad refrain.


