Tourism,wFZyNQAIcdE,UgyK847u00OGleZZvV94AaABAg,,@sapporoichiban3612,"This seems like a travel guide for people with tic toc brain who don’t know how to look after their stuff and always need something to complain about. 

Yes, pickpockets are concentrated in tourist areas, maybe be prepared and you won’t be a victim. 

Yes, there are venders who try and scam with excursions, that is why you book with a travel agent, hotel or another reputable vender. 

In terms of the disappointment with places like Piza, I have been there and I found it to be fantastic because I understood what I was going to see in terms of history and there are literally dimensions of the tower available to anyone, lol. Venice was stinky and pricy but it was incredible, again in terms of history and culture. Maybe book a legit cooking class or take in some entertainment. If you go for just a bridge and a boat ride and you are mad, that is a you problem. Think outside the box, I chose to stay a few extra days in Venice.",2026-05-04T17:02:50Z,2026-05-04T17:02:50Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-18T02:02:12.043374
Tourism,wFZyNQAIcdE,Ugyoezhxv9hw2l6OioB4AaABAg,,@pitacosdomundo4007,"No, I LIVED in Marrakesch for three months and NEVER had any  of the experiences described here. I agree with the Hall of Fame, Cancun, Santorini, the Eiffel tower, having lived in all of those places too but Marrakesh accounts were highly wrong. But I had those experiences in half a day in Tangiers. And I now live in Chefchaouen, and can say that here is really peaceful and harassment free.",2026-05-04T16:16:02Z,2026-05-04T16:16:02Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-18T02:02:12.043377
