Tourism,wFZyNQAIcdE,UgzejzY17c26_EM0jRJ4AaABAg,,@pbinnj3250,"The narrator doesn’t seem familiar with tourism. 1. If you go to Santorini take a cooking class and don’t miss the drag show at gay hotels. Gay and straight people go. You will never laugh so hard ever again in your life. Take the sunset cruise in the caldera, bring swimming trunks. 2. Time square at night is fantastical. Pair it with a show on broadway and dinner (in the opposite order.) expect exorbitant prices on broadway or go to a matinee. Don’t skimp on tickets, you want a good seat. Everything in New York is expensive. Expect that. 3. Pickpockets are everywhere, especially in Venice and Rome. If you don’t have an anti pickpocket plan, stay home.",2026-05-03T10:58:25Z,2026-05-03T10:58:25Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-18T02:02:12.043425
